    "sentence": "You've got lending conditions tight and getting a little tighter.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230726.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20230726",
    "context_question": "On the—on the credit side, I’m wondering if you saw anything in the—in the latest SLOOS data that made you think you’re getting a quantum of credit contraction beyond what you’d expect. The bank lending data really is—the growth rate’s edging down towards below, heading below zero, which is usually, you know, a recession indicator.",
