    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230726.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20230726",
    "context_question": "Hi, Chair Powell. Rachel Siegel from the Washington Post. Thanks for taking our questions. Could you break down the reasons why inflation has fallen and what share of that credit you would give to factors that don’t stem directly from rate hikes or that might be within your control at all, like easing supply chains and a drop in energy prices over the past year?",
