  {
    "id": "b89e6d33-50db-4e47-829c-9139e002e54e",
    "sentence": "It's not something that only depends on the level of the federal funds rate.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20161214.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20161214",
    "context_question": "Justine Underhill, Yahoo Finance. So the Fed’s balance sheet has grown to over $4 trillion. And as the Fed begins removing policy accommodation, under what circumstances would you see the Fed removing or possibly winding down its balance sheet in either letting mature—securities mature or possibly outright selling bonds from the SOMA portfolio?",
