    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20111102",
    "context_question": "Peter Barnes, Fox Business. Sir, could you comment on the failure of MF Global, which is a primary dealer? And specifically, the Financial Times is reporting that the leverage ratio at MF Global was 40 to 1. Were you aware of that? Did the Fed approve of that? Is that an acceptable leverage ratio, particularly since the financial crisis?",
