  {
    "id": "da9dae7d-4dcc-45e4-b786-7d47022e8093",
    "sentence": "In other words, banks are arranging a lot of these loans.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20190130.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20190130",
    "context_question": "I’m Nancy Marshall-Genzer from Marketplace. I want to talk to you about corporate debt. Are you worried that by taking a pause in raising interest rates—we’ve had low interest rates for so long—are you contributing to a bubble in corporate debt?",
    "top": "",
