  {
    "id": "e10090cd-ba5c-4244-9217-afed015a19ea",
    "sentence": "You can see that either in the household survey or in the payroll establishment survey. So I think there's no doubt that the labor market is considerably better today than it was two years ago, there's not any question about that. But it's also the case that many indicators of the labor market remain quite weak, ranging from the number of long-term unemployed to the number of people who have part-time work who would like full-time work.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20121212.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20121212",
    "context_question": "New jobs versus people leaving.",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
