  {
    "id": "cb8bb5f1-7a3e-44a5-8f63-9ed1b4e28b61",
    "sentence": "Nonetheless, we'll be able to see what's happening with credit conditions -- what's happening with lending.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20230503.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20230503",
    "context_question": "Just to quickly follow up—what does it suggest about the scope for the Committee to pause rate increases perhaps as early as next month, even if the data remains strong then, if, if it’s having some kind of substitute effect?",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "1704442f-6bb7-40b3-a811-48b82fabfbb1",
    "sentence": "It will turn out that inventories were higher. And so you'll see -- you'll see those data revised up.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20250507.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20250507",
    "context_question": "—imported goods has increased significantly. So the impact of the imported inflation may delay. So, what is the impact to your future decision?",
    "top": "",
