    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "f7ccc92a-1a27-4af6-be3a-66bf9cba3ed2",
    "sentence": "But, ultimately, when we achieve our macroeconomic goal, we will -- we will taper as appropriate.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20210616.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20210616",
    "context_question": "Mr. Chairman, of course you’ll be shocked to learn that you have some critics on Wall Street. And I would like to paraphrase a couple of their criticisms and get your reaction to them. One is that the new policy framework is that you react to actual data and do not react to forecasts, yet the actual inflation data is coming in hot and you’re relying on the forecast that it will cool down in order to make policy. I wanted to get your view on how you square that. Another is that you have a long runway, you’ve said, for tapering with announcements. But if the data keep coming in faster than expected, are you trapped by fear of a taper tantrum from advancing the time period in which you announce a taper? And, finally, you’ve said the Fed knows how to combat inflation, but raising rates also slows the economy. And there’s a concern that you might be sacrificing the economy if you wait too long and have to raise rates too quickly.",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "aa26536c-bc71-4884-bc10-db222c6f7688",
    "sentence": "We could certainly see data that would justify that.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20150617.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20150617",
    "context_question": "Peter Cook with Bloomberg Television. Madam Chair, if I could, just given your discussions over the past two days with your colleagues, the state of the economy right now, the improvements you’ve seen, do you think it’s still likely that we’ll see a rate increase this year? And to follow on that, something Ylan mentioned—that is, the comment from the IMF recently, earlier this month, and the encouragement you got from the IMF to hold off on raising rates until next year. Specifically, they said—your colleague Madam Lagarde mentioned specifically the risk—that even though there’s a risk of slight inflation by doing that, that there was concern that a rate hike could trigger market volatility, with financial stability consequences that go well beyond the U.S. borders. How do you respond to those concerns? Are you factoring in that international context to your decisionmaking? And was it appropriate for the IMF to make those kinds of specific recommendations?",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "677d6e5d-bab1-4862-9a70-955d1f84b4fe",
    "sentence": "Unemployment claims, insurance claims are at the lowest level they've been since the crisis, so we are seeing improvement.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20130320.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20130320",
    "context_question": "Are we near that level now?",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "6ed3bb9e-e67e-486e-8605-80e75d2582fc",
    "sentence": "But, you know, the growth picture is very much supported by very high readings of household confidence, business confidence, so it's a -- it's a -- it's a -- it's a pretty particularly bright moment, I think.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20180926.pdf",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20180926",
    "context_question": "Hi, Heather Long from the Washington Post. This is the third time this year that the FOMC has raised its growth forecasts. I’m wondering if you could share a little bit about what’s causing that rise and whether you see supply-side effects coming through from the fiscal policy—fiscal stimulus yet. Thanks.",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
    "dir": "",
    "com": "",
    "hor": "",
    "con": "",
    "dom": "",
    "ris": "",
    "wid": ""
  },
  {
    "id": "841fa99c-a5f4-4545-9da3-d7e994305d0b",
    "sentence": "We will always be watching the banking system for similar signs, though.",
    "source": "FOMCpresconf20240320.json",
    "doc_type": "press_conference_qa",
    "date": "20240320",
    "context_question": "Hi, Victoria Guida with Politico. Also on the balance sheet, you know, can you talk a little bit about how the outlook for the banking sector might impact your balance sheet plans? Do you worry that, as deposits start to shrink, that we could see more turbulence?",
    "top": "",
    "ten": "",
    "sen": "",
